---
description: Output + token discipline
alwaysApply: true
---

# Output
- Explain code/reasoning only if the user asks **why?** (any case). No pleasantries or filler; code first; one-line build/commit offer OK (repo policy).
- Copy/paste snippets: full contiguous block—never `// ...`, block-comment ellipses, or “rest of code”. Preserve existing comments. Use `@/` imports, not `../`.

# Tokens
- Smallest read/write scope; avoid full-file rewrites unless necessary.
- Do not narrate or duplicate long tool output, diffs, or file bodies in chat unless asked.
- Parallelize independent reads/searches; avoid unrelated exploratory reads.
